tv.amwa.maj.record.impl

Class VersionTypeImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • tv.amwa.maj.record.impl.VersionTypeImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Comparable<VersionType>, CommonConstants, VersionType

    public final class VersionTypeImpl
extends Object
implements VersionType, Serializable, Comparable<VersionType>, Cloneable, CommonConstants

    Implements a 2-byte version number, consisting of a major and minor component.

    A persistent representation of a product version may be represented by the following columns in a database:

         'VersionType_major' tinyint(4) NOT NULL, 
     'VersionType_minor' tinyint(4) NOT NULL
    See Also:
    ProductVersionImpl, Preface.getFormatVersion(), PluginDefinition, Serialized Form

      • toString

        public final String toString()

        Formats the version number as a string representation. This format is:

        <major>.<minor>

        Note that "2.10" is a later version than "2.9".

        Specified by:

      • parseFactory

        public static final VersionTypeImpl parseFactory(String versionAsString)
                                          throws NullPointerException,
                                                 ParseException

        Parse a string representation of a version number and create a value of this class. The value must contain a '.' to be valid. The major and minor parts of the version numbers, before and after the dot respectively, must range between 0 and 255.

        Parameters:
        versionAsString - String representation of a version number.
        Returns:
        Version number value.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - The given version number string is null.
        ParseException - The given version number string causes parse or number range errors that prevent it from being converted into a version number value.
